{"questionId":"27628","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a circle with a diameter&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>&nbsp;has coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> has&nbsp;coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find&nbsp;the coordinates of the centre of the circle.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>centre&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; (accept vector notation and/or missing brackets)&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27628","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.3a.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the coordinates of the centre of the circle.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints"],"memberSectionIds":[],"s